                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> <lb n="1"/>descrip<supplied reason="lost">tum et recognitum ex tabu</supplied><lb break="no" n="2"/>la aerea q<supplied reason="lost">uae fixa est Romae in mu</supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/>ro post te<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>mpl</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> divi <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> ad Minervam</supplied> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> ------ sti]<lb break="no" n="2"/>p<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>end</abbr><ex>iis</ex></expan> emeritis <expan><abbr>dimiss</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>honest</abbr><ex>a</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>mission</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> per</supplied> <lb n="3"/>Tere<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ntium</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">quorum nomina</supplied> <lb n="4"/>subs<supplied reason="lost">cripta sunt civitatem Romanam qui</supplied> <lb n="5"/>eorum <supplied reason="lost">non haberent dederunt et conubium</supplied> <lb n="6"/>cum ux<supplied reason="lost">oribus quas postea duxissent dum</supplied><lb break="no" n="7"/>t<supplied reason="lost">a</supplied>xat [singulis ------
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Erhalten ist ein Fragment der tab. I. Datierung: Wahrscheinlich unter Mark Aurel und Lucius Verus (161-169) oder Mark Aurel und Commodus (177-180). Tab. I int.: Z. 5: zwischen &amp;quot;&amp;quot;ux[oribus quas&amp;quot;&amp;quot; und &amp;quot;&amp;quot;postea duxissent&amp;quot;&amp;quot; muß versehentlich die Passage &amp;quot;&amp;quot;tunc habuissent cum est civitas iis data aut cum iis quas&amp;quot;&amp;quot; ausgelassen worden sein. (B): RMD: tab. I int.: Z. 5/6: dum]/taxat.</p>
            </div>
